{"id":6400,"date":"2019-08-08T18:55:02","date_gmt":"2019-08-08T13:25:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/?p=6400"},"modified":"2022-05-23T16:54:15","modified_gmt":"2022-05-23T11:24:15","slug":"virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html","title":{"rendered":"Virtual Reality Applications: Benefits and Use Cases in the Real Estate Industry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-6404\" src=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/virtual-reallity-in-real-estate.jpg\" alt=\"Virtual Reality in Real Estate\" width=\"908\" height=\"441\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/virtual-reallity-in-real-estate.jpg 908w, https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/virtual-reallity-in-real-estate-300x146.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/virtual-reallity-in-real-estate-768x373.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/08\/virtual-reallity-in-real-estate-600x291.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 908px) 100vw, 908px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Regularly, a land operator gives a considerable rundown of properties to the customer. A short time later, there are clarifications, dealings, lastly the official visits to houses. This work process has continued as before for a considerable length of time. However, it&#8217;s poorly implemented and tedious for real estate agents as well as for home buyers too.<\/p>\n<p>There&#8217;s a distinct advantage, and it&#8217;s now changing how the real estate companies use \u2013 <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/virtual-reality-application-development.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Virtual reality app development<\/a><\/strong>. The intensity of VR innovation can help land operators develop their business, get more customers, and convey top-level administrations. It&#8217;s especially critical to embrace this innovation today.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Virtual_Reality_VR_Development\"><\/span>Virtual Reality (VR) Development<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Virtual reality offers an immersive digital recreation of a real-life setting or environment and emulates a user&#8217;s physical environment to create a truly immersive and interactive experience. But why is the experience so immersive?<\/p>\n<p>This is mainly because users are actually blocked out and can only view the virtual world and objects.<br \/>\nIt&#8217;s the most immersive experience \u2013 the as the real world is phased out to let users see the virtual world and virtual objects around them.<\/p>\n<p>To experience VR, it is essential to have equipment such as Google Cardboard to headsets like Samsung Gear, Oculus Rift, and HTC Vive. The focus of VR activity is towards creating emotional experiences to build an emotional engagement.<\/p>\n<p>VR also provides a uniform real estate and the banking experience for the customer, which reduces the bottlenecks and pains of scheduling appointments with customers, sellers, agents and bankers.<\/p>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\n<li><strong>Easy Access:<\/strong> Cost of acquisition and development of both hardware and software used to access AR and VR has become relatively simple.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Platform Support:<\/strong> Unity provides an open-source developer platform and strong learning support for aspiring community members. Youtube recently launched its 360 video channel and is providing free camera equipment to some content creators.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Internet of Things Ecosystem:<\/strong> Entire connected ecosystem, beacons, and network data allow tracking the customer journey across channels and open the door to take AR\/VR into a multi-layered consumer environment.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Virtual_Reality_in_Real_Estate\"><\/span>Virtual Reality in Real Estate<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>The entire procedure of buying property is simplified with a mobile app. Prospective buyers can now log to real estate app to get a virtual view. They can seek a list of specific real estate properties. Upon selection of ownership, the customer can wear a VR headset to gain the virtual experience of exploring the property.<\/p>\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">\n<li>Customers can view the property, and the sales executive can confirm the principal approval with AI robotic processes to retrieve the credit score and financial details to accurately determine the mortgage amount.<\/li>\n<li>Mortgage limits and property details will be displayed in the VR headset for the customer to view.<\/li>\n<li>Using hand controllers, customers can show interest in a property, view another feature or seek additional information.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>When it comes to purchasing a house or real estate property, it&#8217;s now possible for prospective buyers to connect to a mobile app to communicate with a real estate agent and interact with a virtual agent (voice bot).<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_You_Can_Use_Virtual_Reality_in_the_Real_Estate_Business\"><\/span>How You Can Use Virtual Reality in the Real Estate Business<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Virtual_Property_Tours\"><\/span>Virtual Property Tours<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Virtual property tours are making the process of finding properties easy, hassle-free and convenient. To make the process more efficient and immersive realtors can offer virtual property tours on their websites with the help of virtual reality. When a potential buyer check clicks on the house, the site will display the virtual tours. This feature can facilitate the buyer to conduct a virtual tour of every room with the help of virtual reality glasses. The tour can incorporate a virtual guide that allows buyers through different places and narrates the relevant information about various features of the house.<\/p>\n<p>If a prospective buyer clicks on a house, the website will provide a &#8216;virtual tour&#8217; option for selected property.<\/p>\n<p>Also, virtual tours can let potential buyers to seamlessly interact with surrounding objects. Similar trips can be created for commercial spaces to help business owners identify a suitable workspace. With virtual reality in the real estate industry, potential buyers can save time and find out multiple properties anytime and from any location.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Virtual_Showcase_of_Property\"><\/span>Virtual Showcase of Property<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Customers visit different real estate properties before choosing the one they need which often require time and resources. If the property is located far away from the customer&#8217;s current location, it might cause hassles for property owner. For this situation, VR technology solutions allow prospective buyers to visit properties putting a VR headset and experience immersive walkthrough of properties.<\/p>\n<p>Although organizing is an extraordinary method to showcase properties, it requires speculation, especially in case you&#8217;re selling recently fabricated properties. Computer-generated reality innovation is an unusual path for real estate brokers to market related properties with almost no speculation.<\/p>\n<p>Organizations, for example, roomy offer VR arranging administrations to land specialists. VR enables you to make staggering 3D land visits and get properties arranged with the goal that your customers can look at them.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Interior_Design\"><\/span>Interior Design<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Interior designers and architects very often take extensive time to create 3D design layouts for houses. With <strong>virtual reality in real estate<\/strong>, interior designers can exhibit their designs via VR glasses. Interior designing firms can create multiple virtual designs for clients. These design can accentuate color scheme, layout, area, and rooms. Clients can ask for changes in the design. Alternatively, the designer can update such alterations in real-time. Virtual reality can be an effective solution for interior designers.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 40px;\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Engineering_Visualization\"><\/span>Engineering Visualization<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>It showcases a property that isn&#8217;t built at this point and has dependably been a test for land designers and specialists. Users must have come across huge three-dimensional models that demonstrate different property or neighborhood and these models help potential purchasers envision engineering.<\/p>\n<p>With regard to these new developments, land operators make enormous showrooms with full-scale models. Obviously, these showcasing techniques require extensive speculation. Computer-generated reality can successfully overcome this roadblock and allow potential homebuyers to look at both the outside and inside of yet-to-be-constructed properties.<\/p>\n<h4 style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 42px; color: #0a57f4;\">Conclusion<\/h4>\n<p>Immersive and sophisticated virtual reality experiences will rule the future. Several technology companies can help real estate agents create immersive real estate <a href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/ar-vr-app-development.html\">VR apps<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_47_1 ez-toc-wrap-left counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-transparent ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Virtual_Reality_VR_Development\" title=\"Virtual Reality (VR) Development\">Virtual Reality (VR) Development<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Virtual_Reality_in_Real_Estate\" title=\"Virtual Reality in Real Estate\">Virtual Reality in Real Estate<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#How_You_Can_Use_Virtual_Reality_in_the_Real_Estate_Business\" title=\"How You Can Use Virtual Reality in the Real Estate Business\">How You Can Use Virtual Reality in the Real Estate Business<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Virtual_Property_Tours\" title=\"Virtual Property Tours\">Virtual Property Tours<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Virtual_Showcase_of_Property\" title=\"Virtual Showcase of Property\">Virtual Showcase of Property<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Interior_Design\" title=\"Interior Design\">Interior Design<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/virtual-reality-in-real-estate-benefits-and-use-cases.html\/#Engineering_Visualization\" title=\"Engineering Visualization\">Engineering Visualization<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Regularly, a land operator gives a considerable rundown of properties to the customer. A short time later, there are clarifications, dealings, lastly the official visits to houses. This work process has continued as before for a considerable length of time. However, it&#8217;s poorly implemented and tedious for real estate agents as well as for home [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6404,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"ngg_post_thumbnail":0},"categories":[1546,1586],"tags":[1281,1729,1733],"acf":{"show_blog_end":"yes","add_blog_end":"<div style=\"display: inline-block; background: #fdfdfd; border: 1px solid #eeefef; padding: 5%; width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\r\n<h5 style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 25px; border-bottom: 1px solid #dcdede; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 10px; padding-bottom: 5px; font-family: 'Open Sans',sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: #000; width: 100%;\">Related Posts<\/h5>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/understanding-of-ar-vr-and-mixed-reality.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Understanding AR, VR and Mixed Reality<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/